I have successfully created all three files required for the redesign, creating a cohesive, premium light-mode UI reminiscent of FreshBooks and Stripe.

1. **`design-brief.md`**: Outlines the new high-contrast light mode design system, color tokens (Indigo/Emerald/Amber/Red/Blue), typography scale, robust spacing system, and component guidelines. It effectively translates the strategic goals from the STACK and research briefs into an actionable UI system.
2. **`landing-prototype.html`**: A fully responsive, modern marketing website mockup. It features a sticky navigation bar, a high-impact hero section with a dashboard preview placeholder, a feature grid (using inline SVG icons), a simple dual-tier pricing section, and a full footer. 
3. **`app-prototype.html`**: A comprehensive in-app UI mockup that maps all screens outlined in the `functional-spec.md`. It includes a custom navigation widget in the bottom right corner (a "Prototype Navigation Control") that allows you to click through the different views instantly:
   - Auth flows (Login screen)
   - App Shell (Sidebar, Topbar)
   - Dashboard (Stat cards, recent invoices table)
   - Invoices List (Filter controls, tables)
   - Invoice Detail (Document view)
   - Invoice Form (Creation/Editing with line items)
   - Clients List
   - Settings (Business Profile)

Both HTML files use plain HTML+CSS with minimal vanilla JS for interactive state switching, utilizing zero external dependencies (SVG icons are baked directly into the markup). They adhere strictly to the shared design brief for a cohesive aesthetic.
